abstract: TWENTY-TWO days almost to the hour after Tug McGraw was saluted in a downtown Philadelphia parade as a World Series folk  hero, he was snubbed in baseball's draft for its free-agent auction. Not merely insulted at being chosen by only a few teams in the late rounds, but ignored completely.

abstract: "AMERICA'S not gonna be pushed around anymore," says Frank  Sinatra. So do Gregory Peck, Bill Cosby, Angie Dickinson, Ernest Borgnine, Johnny Cash, Saily Struthers, plus a showroom full of other stars. They are helping to remind Americans that the desperate Chrysler Corporation has some "K" cars to sell.
